
### NMState

[NMState](https://nmstate.io/) is is a library and CLI tool (nmstatectl) used to manage Linux host networking settings in a declarative manner. 

Instead of running a series of manual commands (imperative approach), you describe the desired network state (e.g., IP addresses, routes, DNS, or bridges) using a structured **YAML** or **JSON** schema. `Nmstate` then calculates the difference between the current and desired states and applies only the necessary changes.

NMState is very similar to the Canonical [NetPlan](https://netplan.readthedocs.io/en/stable/), as both are declarative networking tools that use YAML files to define a "desired state" rather than requiring manual commands.


### NMState Operator

The [**Kubernetes NMState Operator**](https://operatorhub.io/operator/kubernetes-nmstate-operator) is a layer built on top of the NMState engine specifically for **Kubernetes** and **OpenShift** clusters.   


NodeNetworkState (NNS) - to display the network state

NodeNetworkConfigurationPolicy (NNCP) - to define the desired network state

NodeNetworkConfigurationEnactement (NNCE) - to reconcile the NNS with the NNCP.

PlacementRule to configure on which node the VM should run.



## DEMO

### Check the NMState Operator is installed

oc get operators | grep -i nmstate

oc get all -n openshift-nmstate

### Create a NMState Custom Resource

In order to configure the NMState Operator, a NMState Custom Resource needs to be created if not already done.

OpenShift Web Console > Installed Operators > `openshift-nmstate` project > **Kubernetes NMState Operator** > Create instance > Leave all values to default and click **Create**


### Create a Node Network Configuration Policy

Create a `Node Network Configuration Policy` to configure an OVS bridge using the `ens4` interface

OCP Web Console > Node Network Configuration Policy

- Policy Name: br0-ovs-ens4
- Interace name: br0-ovs
- Type: Open vSwitch bridge
- IP Configuration: IPv4 - DHCP
- Port: ens4

**Open vSwitch bridge mapping**

- OVN localnet name: br0-network
- OVS bridge name: br0-ovs


### Create a Network Attachment Definition

Create a Network Attachment Definition and map it to the `br0-network` OVS localnet logical network.

- Name: br0-network
- Network Type: OVN Kubernetes secondary localnet network
- Bridge mapping: br0-network

### Attach Network Attachment Definition to a VM

Add the NAD to a VM

